==Romanian==
===Noun===
'''zârnă''' {{f}}, plural ''[[zârne]]''
#The Black nightshade, also known as sunberry. [[Latin]], ''[[Solanum nigrum]]''.

===Etymology===
Disputed. May be from a pre-Roman language, such as Dacian or Thracian, comparisons having been made to the Dacian name for a plant of the genus ''[[Hellebore|Helleborus]]'': ''[[Prodiarna]]'' (''diarna'' --> ''zârnă''). Cf. Paliga, et al.

The [[W:Romanian Academy|Romanian Academy]] in its official dictionary, the ''Dicţionarul explicativ al limbii române'' (1998), however, derives the word from [[Old Slavonic]] ''[[zrŭno]]'', "a berry" or "a grain" [http://dexonline.ro/search.php?cuv=zarna&source=].

